headline: Self-driving vehicle startup Nuro valued at $6 billion in late-stage funding round
summary: The latest tranche of $97 million follows the $106 million announced in April, which included investors such as T. Rowe Price, Fidelity, and Tiger Global.  Many startups that became unicorns during the 2021 funding boom are now raising capital at lower valuations as investors' attention turns toward artificial intelligence.  Nuro has been pushing to scale its self-driving platform and expand commercial partnerships.
